# 3. たよれる仲間

Emu: Humhumhumm♪ I'm the first one here!
Emu: Lemme get my sketchbook and pens out and...
Emu: Get started on Operation: Exciting Weed Pulling Poster☆
Emu: My poster's gonna make pulling weeds look like so much fun that everyone's going to come join us!
Emu: I'll have it say, “Fun volunteer opportunity! Come pull weeds with us!”
Emu: Where should I write the date...? Hmm...
Emu: Oh, that reminds me! The posters for our shows always put that towards the bottom!
Emu: Then, I'll put the date somewhere around there, and have a picture of people pulling weeds in the middle!
Emu: Humhumhummｍ♪ Pulling weeds with everyone is so much fun♪
Honami: Oh, Emu, you are here!
Emu: Morning, Honami☆
Honami: Hehe. Good morning. I just happened to hear your voice while working on some things for the cleanup committee.
Honami: Huh? What are you drawing?
Emu: Oh, this?! Check it out! Ta-daa!
Honami: “Fun volunteer opportunity! Come pull weeds with us!”...?
Emu: Yup! I've been asked to volunteer to pull weeds as a class rep!
Emu: And I was just working on a poster that's going to get more people to join us!
Honami: I see. These people pulling weeds have such lovely smiles on their faces.
Honami: This should help convince others that pulling weeds can be very fun.
Emu: You think so? Thank goodness!
Emu: Oh, I know! I bet this poster would become even more wonderhoy if you drew something, Honami!
Honami: What?
Emu: I really love the way you draw because they're such a great expression of your feelings! They always look sparkly and fluffy and fuzzy and stuff!
Honami: Emu...
Emu: And I always love looking at them because they're so explosively eye-opening, like kapow!
Honami: (I-I'm not sure if that counts as praise...)
Honami: Thank you, Emu... Then, why don't I draw a little picture in this corner?
Emu: Yay!
Honami: How does this look...?
Emu: Oh, that's really cute!!
Emu: Is that a butterfly?
Honami: No, it's supposed to be a flower.
Honami: I thought that more flowers will be able to bloom once all the weeds have been pulled.
Emu: Oh, now I see! These little stick thingies must be the stamens, and the white flappy parts are the petals!
Honami: I apologize if it was hard to tell. Anyway, I should get going...
Emu: No, wait! Can you draw more flowers for me?!
Honami: Huh?
Emu: I feel like that'll make this poster cuter and more fun!
Honami: Then, I'll draw a few more.
Emu: Thanks!
Emu: (Hehe. Thanks to Honami, this poster's gonna look super wonderhoy!)
Emu: (I can't wait to show it to Asahina!)
Honami: If you don't mind, I'll use these chopsticks.
Kanade: *Nod* Umm... I've served everyone a bowl of rice, so I think we're ready to eat.
Mafuyu: Okay.
Mafuyu, Honami & Kanade: Let's eat.
Honami: Thank you for having me over again today. And for allowing me to join you for dinner.
Kanade: No, thank you.
Kanade: My grandmother sent over a big box of vegetables, but they won't stay fresh for long. So, I'm glad you're here to help us get through them.
Honami: Hehe. I'm also glad. But please feel free to have as much as you like, you two. These braised eggplants turned out even better than they did last time.
Mafuyu: Thank you.
Mafuyu: ...
Honami: ...?
Kanade: You've looked really tired lately, Mafuyu.
Honami: It has been very hot this summer. If you like, I can make something that's easier on the stomach.
Mafuyu: No, that's okay. I was just thinking about something.
Honami: Is something on your mind?
Mafuyu: Yes.
Mafuyu: I've been asked to run a volunteer weeding program as part of my class representative duties, but we've been having trouble recruiting people...
Honami: Weeding...? Will you be doing that with Emu?
Mafuyu: Yes, how did you know...?
Honami: Oh, I just happened to come across Emu drawing a poster for it the other day.
Mafuyu: Ah, I see.
Kanade: Recruiting people for that sounds really hard...
Mafuyu: It is. Especially since it's been so hot this year. No one seems interested.
Mafuyu: Which is why I was thinking about other ways to get the word out.
Honami: ...
Emu: And I was just working on a poster that's going to get more people to join us!
Mafuyu: Hmm... I just checked the sign-up sheet, but it seems there haven't been any new volunteers.
Emu: Okay...
Emu: Hmm... What can we do to make it so people want to come join us...?
Mafuyu: Well... Our remaining options are...
???: Pardon me.
Honami: Emu, Asahina, do you two have a minute?
Emu: Huh? Honami? Is something the matter? Are you here to do cleanup committee stuff?
Honami: No. So...
Honami: If you're both okay with it, I'd like to volunteer to help pull weeds.
Mafuyu: What?
Emu: R-Really?! You'll come pull weeds with us?!
Honami: Yes. Also...
Honami: Would it be alright if I helped a little with running this event? I feel like I want to lend you two a hand after seeing you putting in so much effort.
Emu: H-Honami!!
Mafuyu: Thank you, Mochizuki. Then, I think we'll gladly accept your kind offer.
Emu: Yeah, let's do our best together!
Honami: Yes, let's!
Honami: So, I take it no one else has signed up to help?
Mafuyu: *Nod* As far as volunteer work goes, it appears that this seems the most taxing in everyone's minds.
Honami: Right. It does involve manual labor...
Emu: Hmm... But I still think working together to make everything look pretty is gonna be a lot of fun.
Honami: Fun...
Honami: Oh... What if we tried a new angle?
Mafuyu: A new angle...?
Honami: Yes. For example, if all participants are promised a delicious meal, then they'll know that their hard work will be rewarded in the end.
Emu: Oh, that's really good!
Honami: Oh, but you'll have budget constraints to think about, so I'm sure we can't do anything lavish like that.
Mafuyu: No, I agree. That is a good idea.
Mafuyu: We should be upfront about how tough this is going to be, but also show that it can be very fun and rewarding. That should help convince people.
Emu: Tough, but also fun...
Emu: (But how do we make this fun? What would convince people to come pull weeds with us...?)
Emu: (How do we get the attention of all the school students, elderly residents and small children...?)
Emu: Hmm...
Emu: I know! Asahina! Honami!
Emu: We should take this opportunity to go there for ourselves and investigate!
Mafuyu & Honami: Investigate...?
